column2: "Ah, Mister Kotoshiro."
"<%me>. Matoi. Lady Sukuna-hime has awakened, and she wishes to have an audience with the both of you."
"Audience, you say? Isn't that too heavy a word to use? One merely wishes to meet them, there is no need to be so fretful."
"Kotoshiro, cease that posture. Relax thy body and be at ease. Thou shalt never be wed if thou art so austere."
"Milady. Please refrain from speaking unnecessary words."
"Of course, one is well aware. Striking where it hurts, is it not efficient?"
"Erm... Lady Sukuna-hime?"
"What have we? Do not be so reserved in one's presence."
"I am the Miko of Harkotan, not of thou. "
"But, behaving so crudely towards a Deity..."
"Crude? Such nonsense! It is but one's request."
"Well, If thou art so reserved, one shall command thee, though one prefers not to."
"1. I got it, Sukuna-hime"
"2. Understood, Lady Sukuna-hime"
"Kaka! That will do."
"Dost thou not understand? Thou art... teasing me? That is a tasteless pastime, to tease a Deity."
"Be that as it may, thou art quite meddlesome."
"Though thou may have ties with the troublesome dark ones colluding with the Kuronites, there should not be a need to be with this fool."
"Rather, you shouldst strike your enemies with this fool as a bait. Why did you not do so?"
"You might be right, but we can't just leave him."
"That's all?"
"I think that's it..."
"Kaka! Thou art amusing. I feel honored to have met thee."
"After decades and centuries, one has finally found an existence one could call friend. One is surely blessed to hast met thou."
"Friend, but I'm..."
"What is this, art thou displeased? Or art thou incapable of calling a Deity friend?"
"No, that's not what I mean..."
"Is it not fine, then? I have decided to call the both of you friend. I do not mind even if 'tis not reciprocal."
"...Lady Sukuna-hime."
"Honorifics."
"Ah, erm... Nice to meet you, Sukuna-hime."
"Kaka! Likewise."
